Wanted to test it but found out that parameters are not yet supported. Are they in scope for 4.1? I guess so, they are in the public API.
I wrote this test:
@Test
public void test() {
    TestHazelcastInstanceFactory factory = new TestHazelcastInstanceFactory();
    HazelcastInstance inst = factory.newHazelcastInstance();
    IMap<Object, Object> map = inst.getMap("map");
    map.put("05", "05");
    map.put("5", "5");

    executeAndPrint(inst, "select __key from map where this=?", "05");
    executeAndPrint(inst, "select __key from map where this=?", 5);
    ((SqlServiceImpl) inst.getSql()).getPlanCache().clear();
    System.out.println("plan cache invalidated");
    executeAndPrint(inst, "select __key from map where this=?", 5);
}

private void executeAndPrint(HazelcastInstance inst, String sql, Object ... params) {
    System.out.println("params: " + Arrays.stream(params)
                                          .map(p -> p.getClass().getSimpleName() + " " + p)
                                          .collect(Collectors.joining(",")));
    for (SqlRow r : inst.getSql().query(sql, params)) {
        System.out.println(r);
    }
    System.out.println("----");
}
I expect this output:
params: String 05
[__key VARCHAR=05]
params: Integer 5
[__key VARCHAR=5]
plan cache invalidated
params: Integer 5
[__key VARCHAR=05]
[__key VARCHAR=5]

That is, the first query will have VARCHAR parameter and will get cached, including the parameter type. The second query will have INT parameter. The cached plan will be used, the INT will be casted to VARCHAR and used in the filter. After invalidating the plan cache, new plan will be created, this time with INT parameter. The field will be casted to INT and this time, both entries will be returned.
Maybe the key in the plan cache should also include parameter types.

